chore(package): change turbo workspace to private

This doesn't mean this is a private repository, but simply that npm will
refuse to publish the package (not the sub-packages) if it's attempted;
see https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/configuring-npm/package-json#private

This also allows yarn users, although officially unsuppored by CES, to
use the top-level repo with one less workaround.
chore(package): "re-enable" husky via adding prepare: "husky install"

chore(pre-commit) use lint-staged to run prettier:

pretty-quick (previously used) has not been updated in 18 months, and is
now broken on newer versions of prettier. We use lint-staged instead to
run prettier on the codebase pre-commit.

See: https://github.com/azz/pretty-quick/issues/168w
